---
description: PR readiness rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Before PR, provide implementation summary, changed files, tests added or
updated, test results, known risks, doc updates, and reviewer notes.

Do not push directly to `main`, `master`, or the repository default branch
unless the user explicitly asks for that exact behavior. Work from a feature/fix
branch, run PR readiness checks, then open a PR.

If feature metadata exists, include feature ID, release ID, ticket scope,
acceptance criteria, doc delta status, QA notes, and release mismatch risks.
